latestPosts.caption:
One day in the life of a working mom - Oh! A toddler mum, mind you! 🫣

Multi-tasking, work-life balance, mom guilt… all are such a huge part of my life now and I’m sure any working mother’s life. 😅

🍦I want to bring up my child in the best possible way but also don’t want to compromise on my dreams and passions (and, I have a few!) 😬. 

🍦I want to ensure I am there for every important event in my child’s life but also need my me-time. Self love, self worth and self esteem are important mantras for me. 🧘🏻‍♀️

The challenge lies in dividing the days, hours and minutes between the two - my work and career growth on one side and my family and motherhood on the other. Work gives me a sense of achievement but my daughter completes me 💚

On days where it seems overwhelming and unmanageable, I think of my mum who studied and worked after having 2 daughters by the age of 22! 🤯 She really is my biggest strength and inspiration!! Love you the most, Ma 🙌

And on days even that doesn’t seem to help, then I have no choice but to sneak in a wine and whine session 🍷😆

Are you a working parent? How do you manage your time between the two? 😊

#workingmom #workingparent #multitasking #worklifebalance #momguiltisreal #momanddaughter #girlmom

Race Report | @hyroxindia Delhi Men’s Doubles
1:36:11. Rank #5 (missed the #4 by a second) This wasn’t just a finish time — it was the outcome of relentless discipline, grit, and grind. Two months of showing up, pushing limits, & staying focused. And in the end @hamidahmed77 & I didn’t just race — we showed up for ourselves & each other.
What began as a casual joke — “Let’s do Hyrox together!” — turned into the most meaningful & fun journeys I’ve ever been on. From building our own workouts, obsessing over reels and rules, strategizing like pros, crafting nutrition plans, to pulling each other’s leg & managing those silent waves of anxiety… We did it all, We did it together.
For me, this block became more than training — it was healing. Coming out of a personal loss, this gave me purpose, structure, & hope. Every Friday at @calfuncdelhi from June 13th, & those extra sessions with Hamid & Sana — became my anchor.
Hamid — watching you evolve was inspiring. From setting audacious goals to sticking to your regime like a monk — your dedication lit the fire in me. You never skipped, never sulked, never stepped back. Just pure heart & hustle. I couldn’t have asked for a better partner — but I am claiming the copyright on Men’s Doubles! 😄
@sana_onthegram — our sounding board, teammate, therapist — all rolled into one. The 3 Musketeers weren’t complete without ur sharp eye, constant nudging & steady support (and occasional panic 😅). We owe you big! I wish there was a Team of 3 at Hyrox - We would have been a Stellar Team
@aamnaa1 @shaifali_n — Our Hype Squad! From handling our Hyrox madness to our race day nutrition & screaming the loudest in the arena — You’re Legends & ⭐️ @johaisohay 
@tomthecat.alyst @md_asif16 — thank you for every correction, tip, & the push. You shaped us.
This wasn’t just a race. It was a story of belief, courage & perseverance. A team that showed up for each other every single time. Nothing more can make me proud than seeing us conquer our biggest fear & turning it in a success story!! A TEAM forever ❤️ Let’s chase bigger goals!
And MAA, this one’s for you. I hope you smiled on Saturday ❤️

latestPosts.caption:
Today feels slow and purposeless because the last month has felt like being on an adrenaline wave with these two! @hamidahmed77 @iamrohitpathak 

From Day 1 to D-Day, I’ve been witness to their @hyroxindia journey. The super early mornings, the grind, the grit, the mental strength to show up despite all odds, syncing our calendars so none of us missed a session together, the shared jokes, the shared anxiety, discussing and re-discussing strategies, giving each other wake up calls… this became more than just a training block! It was a shared goal that the only way for us to conquer was - together!

Hamid, Rohit - I’m beyond proud of what you’ve achieved .. not just on race day but also through the entire process of training for it. SO much respect! ❤️

@iamrohitpathak - I don’t know what has moved me more - you in the role of a coach or you as that rock solid friend who won’t even let an expression of mine go unaddressed. Showing up on 2 hours of sleep to make us workout is only something you can do! 🫡 Stay you, my friend! You’re all heart! 🤗

@hamidahmed77 - I saw a new side of you this month. You put your mind to something you’ve never done before and you smashed it in style! 🙌 Although now I can claim that I’ve taught you the correct way to squat 🤪 Thank you for being my silent supporter, even when I don’t know it and guess what, this journey has just begun! 😬

CONGRATULATIONS MY BOYS! You did it!🥂 

A-team forever!! 🩵 

Eyes on the next one, now?! 😉

Oh what a party it was at the @apollotyresnewdelhimarathon ! 🥳 If you were running it, you couldn’t have missed the AR cheering zone with music, dhol walas, cheers on loudspeakers and some funny posters ! 🎊

Cheering is serious business - From 5:30 am - 10:30 am, on the course screaming and singing our lungs out for each and every runner who crossed us. 🎉

I ran with some, I danced with some , helped a few with bananas and hydration and at the end of the morning, with a full heart, told myself if I’m not running a particular race I will be there on the course encouraging the others to successfully finish theirs! 🙌 

It’s not a joke but just one cheer from us can really egg on a runner who’s already exhausted, maybe in pain and struggling with their mental (and physical) demons! You should try it too !🙃

@johaisohay - Leading from the front! 📣 Hope you get your voice back soon 😅

#AdidasRunnersDel
@adidasrunners

‘Back to school’ days are the best! 🌟

Still reeling under the effects of organising and playing in the parents sports day. With less than 10 days to pull off this event, I’d say we did a pretty decent job! 😬 The way the Shri community comes together time after time is truly unmatched! ❣️

Icing on the cake was having my mini-me right beside me, cheering, supporting and being my water girl from 8 am - 4pm without any meltdowns 😅❤️. 

I firmly believe that if you want your children to develop a love for sports, show them how it’s done - the hard work, the sacrifices, the consistency, the failures and the wins. There really is no better teacher! 🙌

Okay, now back to icing my aches and pains! 😅

TMM’25 done ✅ 

This was my first half-marathon without any regular runs preceding it, my brain was a mess and I wasn’t sure how this would go BUT the crazy energy on the course - the supporters and the vibe - made it so much fun to just glide through the 21kms that I honestly don’t remember suffering through this one! 😅 

Always helps to have your pack supporting you through the pre-run jitters and the post-run aches! @adidasrunners 🫶 

@tatamummarathon

latestPosts.caption:
It never is about one finish line. It’s about all those mornings we make it to and all those nights we let go off! You couldn’t have framed it better, @johaisohay 🤩

A super hard and hardcore training block for me leading up to @delhihalfmarathon .  Getting back post a six month antibiotic course wasn’t easy - my heart rate was out of whack during most of the runs, leaving me completely disheartened but @iamrohitpathak took it upon himself to ensure I reach my goal on race day, injury and sickness free! 🫶

Pausing your social life, family outings for 4 am mornings is never easy but when you have a community like @adidasrunners and a family like mine (@ritutalwar4 , @chandhiok , @karanchandhiok ) knowing every single person out there has your back and is rooting for you like their life depends on it, it makes it SO worth your while. ❣️

While crossing this finish line, holding my stomach (last 3 kms I ran with a bad stitch), I couldn’t help break into tears knowing soooo many people worked with me to make this possible! @liftwithrajat - here’s looking at you too! 😉 To all of you - I am forever grateful. 🙏

Running, I AM BACK! 🏃🏻‍♀️Let’s do this! ⚡️….. just after the pollution break!😷

latestPosts.caption:
After over 2 years dedicated to building @tapr.pay , it’s time for me to embark on a new challenge.

Feeling a mix of emotions as I bid farewell to this chapter - almost like a breakup, but as someone wise said, “When one door closes, another one opens.” 

With a heavy yet hopeful heart, I’m taking a short break to do all the things I love while eagerly anticipating what lies ahead!

Current things on my to-do list:

🏃🏻‍♀️Run a Half Marathon (or two!)

⛱️ Take a holiday with my parents

🧑‍🧑‍🧒 Spend quality time with my daughter doing all the things she couldn’t while I was at work

 📊 Do a course to up-skill (wondering which one though! Any suggestions on good marketing/ entrepreneurial / strategy courses?) 

Let me know what else I should tick off my bucket list! 🙃

#OnABreak
